<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="298" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Hale</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 25.]</seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Agency and Consulate General of the
                                        U. S. of America</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Alexandria,
                                        Egypt,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-05"><hi rend="italic">May</hi> 5, 1865.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to report that his
                            Highness the Pacha of Egypt has seized the earliest opportunity to
                            express to me the pain with which he has heard the sad tidings of the
                            assassination of the President of the United States; his detestation of
                            the abominable crime, and his sympathy for our country in the grievous
                            loss we have sustained.</p>
                        <p>I have the honor to be, sir, most respectfully, your obedient
                            servant,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>CHARLES HALE.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>